The title of '''High Admiral''' was used by the [[Commander/Legends|commander]] of [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]] forces within an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Sector Group/Legends|Sector Group]]. The title was usually granted to the [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] who led the [[Sector/Legends|sector]]. If the sector was involved in continuous naval actions, the Sector Group's high admiral was a distinct individual from the Moff, so that the Moff did not have to constantly devote their time to the conflict.<ref name="Imperial Sourcebook" /> During the [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial Era]], [[Markand]] served as a high admiral, and at one point received a copy of a message from [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Mirash Peet]] of [[Indupar]] to [[Commodore/Legends|Commodore]] [[Gor Lequar]].<ref name="Pirates & Privateers">''[[Pirates & Privateers]]''</ref> [[Warlord of the Empire]] [[Zsinj]] was promoted to Grand Moff<ref name="Atlas">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> and as High Admiral of [[Crimson Command]]<ref name="Warlords">{{SW|url=news/the-imperial-warlords-despoilers-of-an-empire-part-2|series=The Imperial Warlords: Despoilers of an Empire|text=Part 2|nolive=1}}</ref> following the [[blockade of Dathomir]].<ref name="NEGC">''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]''</ref> After some [[time]], Warlord Zsinj promoted [[Treuten Teradoc]] as high admiral of Crimson Command.<ref name="Warlords" />
{{Stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The title of High Admiral was introduced in the ''[[Imperial Sourcebook]]''; the same publication shows a rank plaque for a Priority Sector High Commander<ref name="Imperial Sourcebook" /> which corresponds to the badge worn by Grand Moff [[Wilhuff Tarkin/Legends|Wilhuff Tarkin]] in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']].<ref name="Episode IV">{{Film|IV}}</ref>

